Many motives doubtless were acting at once on the poet's mind. Venus was symbol of the all—pervading living force of nature3 she was s legendary mother of the Romans: Mars ruled the first, she the second month of spring and the year. Mars indeed in the old Italian mythology was the youthful and beneficent god of plenty, father of the Latin races: ‘cum hodieque’ says Macrob. sat. 1 12 8 ‘in sacris Martem patrem, Venerem genetricem vocemus’.
